id="dsq-comment-message-1674" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Now that there is no official US$ debt ceiling anymore, time has probably come to devalue the $ exchange rate against gold as to avert falling in the deepening fiscal cliff. That&#8217;s how the $-regime keeps the $-reserve trustworthy (solvent and stable) worldwide  All currencies with revaluating goldreserves, rise in tandem against the $. Rising goldprices protect (compensate) against declining $-reserve.Let the goldprice float against the failing $-regime or the goldvalue advocates take all physical gold out of the goldprice manipulating forces.<br
/> A conditio sino qua non for the valueless electronic dollar &amp; gold to keep rolling. A strange form of informal stability, indeed.</p></div></div></li></ul></div></div><script type="text/javascript">
